  "prompt": "If you are stranded on a desert island, what should you do?",
  "response": "Here are key steps to survive if stranded on a desert island:\n\n1. Remain calm and assess your situation\n2. Find fresh water (highest priority)\n- Look for streams, collect rainwater\n- Purify water by boiling if possible\n\n3. Seek shelter \n- Protect from sun and elements\n- Use natural materials like branches, leaves\n- Stay near the beach for potential rescue\n\n4. Find food\n- Look for fruits, coconuts, edible plants\n- Try fishing or catching small animals\n- Learn basic hunting/gathering skills\n\n5. Signal for rescue\n- Create large, visible signals on beach\n- Use bright clothing or reflective materials\n- Build smoky fires to attract attention\n\n6. First aid and health\n- Treat any injuries\n- Maintain hygiene \n- Protect from sunburn and insects\n\n7. Stay positive and mentally strong\n- Maintain hope\n- Keep busy with survival tasks\n- Create a routine\n\n8. Plan potential navigation/escape\n- Build a raft if possible\n- Learn basic navigation skills\n- Study your surroundings\n\n9. Conserve energy\n- Rest during hottest parts of day\n- Don't overexert yourself\n\n10. Be patient and persistent",
